            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "A great graphical update of a classic game.  A blast when played with multiple players!\r\nStill enjoyable as a single player game."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "226629413",
            "steam_id": "76561198042110859",
            "playtime_minutes": 6296,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "I'm not sure if playing this version is worth the time investment to get the steam achievements when the GOG version is cheaper, better quality, more options, features more add-ons and campaigns, oh yeah and everyone plays on Horn of the Abyss anyway. BUT! If you have the same flavor of autistic fascination as me you will enjoy the hundreds of hours of gameplay without regret. Nothing beats the fortress soundtrack or snowballing 1000 skeletons and one shotting everything. Great game. Sad that I didn't start playing until 2020 when it was out for 30 years already... LOL"
        },
